{
  "id": "RAW_ec3f807a",
  "title": "Gemini 和 Vertex AI：Dataproc ML 库在 Spark 上的应用",
  "url": "https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/data-analytics/gemini-and-vertex-ai-for-spark-with-dataproc-ml-library/",
  "date": "2025-10-03 00:00:00",
  "author": "Brad Miro, Deependra Patel",
  "siteName": "Google Cloud Blog",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p>Many data science teams rely on Apache Spark running on Dataproc managed clusters for powerful, large-scale data preparation. As these teams look to connect their data pipelines directly to machine learning models, there's a clear opportunity to simplify the integration. But running inference on a Spark DataFrame using a model from Vertex AI typically requires custom development, making it complex to build a single, end-to-end workflow.</p>\n    <p>To solve this problem, we are developing a new open-source Python library designed to simplify AI/ML inference for Dataproc. This library connects your Apache Spark jobs to use popular ML frameworks and Vertex AI features, starting with model inference. Because the library is open-sourced, you will be able to use it directly in your application code with full transparency into its operation.</p>\n    <h3><b>How it works</b></h3>\n    <p>Dataproc ML is built to feel familiar to Spark users, following a SparkML-style builder pattern. You configure the model you want to use, and then call .transform() on your DataFrame. Let's look at a few common inference use cases.</p>\n    <ol>\n     <li><b>Apply Gemini models to your Spark data</b></li>\n    </ol>\n    <p>You can apply generative AI models, like Gemini, to columns in your Spark DataFrame. This is useful for tasks like classification, extraction, or summarization at scale. In this example, we take a DataFrame with \"city\" &amp; “country” columns and use Gemini to create a new column by providing a simple prompt.</p>\n    <p>You can test in your local environment by installing from PyPi:</p>\n    <p></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <section>\n    <div class=\"kg99be\" jscontroller=\"vkZm2d\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-text-to-copy=\"pip install dataproc-ml\" soy-skip=\"\" ssk=\"4:dXrt\">\n     <div jsaction=\"click:VTVhdd\" class=\"GaRnv\"></div>\n     <div jscontroller=\"M2lJBf\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-enable-content-editable-input-style=\"false\" data-enable-line-wrapping=\"\" data-read-only=\"\">\n      <div class=\"hg3Lgc qs41qe BEXrzd\" data-loadingmessage=\"Loading...\" jscontroller=\"GFartf\" jsaction=\"animationend:kWijWc;dyRcpb:dyRcpb\" data-active=\"true\" jsname=\"aZ2wEe\">\n       <div class=\"eBrXtc\" aria-live=\"polite\" jsname=\"vyyg5\">Loading...</div>\n       <div jsname=\"Hxlbvc\" class=\"JdM54e\">\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZqnFk co39ub\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fxjES Cn087\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZHXbZe hfsr6b\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fDBOYb EjXFBf\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n      <div dir=\"ltr\">\n       <textarea jsname=\"bqeLof\" class=\"Fdco1c\">pip install dataproc-ml</textarea>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb TxA6Xc\"></p>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p>To deploy/test at scale, create a Dataproc version 2.3-ml cluster:</p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <section>\n    <div class=\"kg99be\" jscontroller=\"vkZm2d\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-text-to-copy=\"gcloud dataproc clusters create my-ml-cluster \\\n  --project=&quot;YOUR_PROJECT_ID&quot; \\\n  --region=&quot;YOUR_REGION&quot; \\\n  --image-version=2.3-ml-ubuntu \\\n  --properties='dataproc:pip.packages=dataproc-ml==0.1'\" soy-skip=\"\" ssk=\"4:dXrt\">\n     <div jsaction=\"click:VTVhdd\" class=\"GaRnv\"></div>\n     <div jscontroller=\"M2lJBf\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-enable-content-editable-input-style=\"false\" data-enable-line-wrapping=\"\" data-read-only=\"\">\n      <div class=\"hg3Lgc qs41qe BEXrzd\" data-loadingmessage=\"Loading...\" jscontroller=\"GFartf\" jsaction=\"animationend:kWijWc;dyRcpb:dyRcpb\" data-active=\"true\" jsname=\"aZ2wEe\">\n       <div class=\"eBrXtc\" aria-live=\"polite\" jsname=\"vyyg5\">Loading...</div>\n       <div jsname=\"Hxlbvc\" class=\"JdM54e\">\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZqnFk co39ub\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fxjES Cn087\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZHXbZe hfsr6b\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fDBOYb EjXFBf\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n      <div dir=\"ltr\">\n       <textarea jsname=\"bqeLof\" class=\"Fdco1c\">gcloud dataproc clusters create my-ml-cluster \\\n  --project=\"YOUR_PROJECT_ID\" \\\n  --region=\"YOUR_REGION\" \\\n  --image-version=2.3-ml-ubuntu \\\n  --properties='dataproc:pip.packages=dataproc-ml==0.1'</textarea>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb TxA6Xc\"></p>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p>Copy this example to a file <i>gemini_spark.py.</i></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <section>\n    <div class=\"kg99be\" jscontroller=\"vkZm2d\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-text-to-copy=\"from pyspark.sql import SparkSession\nfrom google.cloud.dataproc_ml.inference import GenAiModelHandler\n\nspark = SparkSession.builder.getOrCreate()\n\n# Create a sample DataFrame\ndf = spark.createDataFrame([\n    (&quot;London&quot;, &quot;UK&quot;),\n    (&quot;Bengaluru&quot;, &quot;India&quot;),\n    (&quot;Paris&quot;, &quot;France&quot;),\n    (&quot;Tokyo&quot;, &quot;Japan&quot;)\n], [&quot;city&quot;, &quot;country&quot;])\n\n# Configure the model handler. It uses gemini-2.5-flash by default.\ngenai_handler = GenAiModelHandler().prompt(\n    &quot;Write a short, one-line rhyming poem about the experience of visiting {city} in {country}.&quot;\n)\n\n# Apply the model, which will output to a new `predictions` column\ngenai_handler.transform(df).show(truncate=False)\n\n# Output\n# +---------+-------+----------------------------------------------+\n# |city     |country|predictions                                   |\n# +---------+-------+----------------------------------------------+\n# |London   |UK     |Big Ben's loud chime, a magical time!         |\n# |Bengaluru|India  |Bengaluru's green, a vibrant tech scene.      |\n# |Paris    |France |In Paris, I fell for romance at first glance. |\n# |Tokyo    |Japan  |In Tokyo's vibrant pace, a smile upon my face.|\n# +---------+-------+----------------------------------------------+\" soy-skip=\"\" ssk=\"4:dXrt\">\n     <div jsaction=\"click:VTVhdd\" class=\"GaRnv\">lang-py</div>\n     <div jscontroller=\"M2lJBf\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-language=\"lang-py\" data-enable-content-editable-input-style=\"false\" data-enable-line-wrapping=\"\" data-read-only=\"\">\n      <div class=\"hg3Lgc qs41qe BEXrzd\" data-loadingmessage=\"Loading...\" jscontroller=\"GFartf\" jsaction=\"animationend:kWijWc;dyRcpb:dyRcpb\" data-active=\"true\" jsname=\"aZ2wEe\">\n       <div class=\"eBrXtc\" aria-live=\"polite\" jsname=\"vyyg5\">Loading...</div>\n       <div jsname=\"Hxlbvc\" class=\"JdM54e\">\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZqnFk co39ub\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fxjES Cn087\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZHXbZe hfsr6b\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fDBOYb EjXFBf\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n      <div dir=\"ltr\">\n       <textarea jsname=\"bqeLof\" class=\"Fdco1c\">from pyspark.sql import SparkSession\nfrom google.cloud.dataproc_ml.inference import GenAiModelHandler\n\nspark = SparkSession.builder.getOrCreate()\n\n# Create a sample DataFrame\ndf = spark.createDataFrame([\n    (\"London\", \"UK\"),\n    (\"Bengaluru\", \"India\"),\n    (\"Paris\", \"France\"),\n    (\"Tokyo\", \"Japan\")\n], [\"city\", \"country\"])\n\n# Configure the model handler. It uses gemini-2.5-flash by default.\ngenai_handler = GenAiModelHandler().prompt(\n    \"Write a short, one-line rhyming poem about the experience of visiting {city} in {country}.\"\n)\n\n# Apply the model, which will output to a new `predictions` column\ngenai_handler.transform(df).show(truncate=False)\n\n# Output\n# +---------+-------+----------------------------------------------+\n# |city     |country|predictions                                   |\n# +---------+-------+----------------------------------------------+\n# |London   |UK     |Big Ben's loud chime, a magical time!         |\n# |Bengaluru|India  |Bengaluru's green, a vibrant tech scene.      |\n# |Paris    |France |In Paris, I fell for romance at first glance. |\n# |Tokyo    |Japan  |In Tokyo's vibrant pace, a smile upon my face.|\n# +---------+-------+----------------------------------------------+</textarea>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb TxA6Xc\"></p>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p>The handler is flexible to support customized options, as explained in the <a href=\"https://dataproc-ml.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api.html#google.cloud.dataproc.ml.inference.GenAiModelHandler\" target=\"_blank\">documentation</a>.</p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <section>\n    <div class=\"kg99be\" jscontroller=\"vkZm2d\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-text-to-copy=\"from google.cloud.dataproc_ml.inference import GenAiModelHandler\nfrom vertexai.generative_models import GenerationConfig\n\n# Configure the model handler\ngenai_handler = (\n    GenAiModelHandler()\n    .prompt(&quot;Write a short, one-line rhyming poem about the experience of visiting {city} in {country}.&quot;)\n    .model(&quot;gemini-2.5-pro&quot;)\n    .output_col(&quot;city_poem&quot;)\n    .generation_config(GenerationConfig(temperature=0.7))\n)\" soy-skip=\"\" ssk=\"4:dXrt\">\n     <div jsaction=\"click:VTVhdd\" class=\"GaRnv\">lang-py</div>\n     <div jscontroller=\"M2lJBf\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-language=\"lang-py\" data-enable-content-editable-input-style=\"false\" data-enable-line-wrapping=\"\" data-read-only=\"\">\n      <div class=\"hg3Lgc qs41qe BEXrzd\" data-loadingmessage=\"Loading...\" jscontroller=\"GFartf\" jsaction=\"animationend:kWijWc;dyRcpb:dyRcpb\" data-active=\"true\" jsname=\"aZ2wEe\">\n       <div class=\"eBrXtc\" aria-live=\"polite\" jsname=\"vyyg5\">Loading...</div>\n       <div jsname=\"Hxlbvc\" class=\"JdM54e\">\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZqnFk co39ub\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fxjES Cn087\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZHXbZe hfsr6b\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fDBOYb EjXFBf\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n      <div dir=\"ltr\">\n       <textarea jsname=\"bqeLof\" class=\"Fdco1c\">from google.cloud.dataproc_ml.inference import GenAiModelHandler\nfrom vertexai.generative_models import GenerationConfig\n\n# Configure the model handler\ngenai_handler = (\n    GenAiModelHandler()\n    .prompt(\"Write a short, one-line rhyming poem about the experience of visiting {city} in {country}.\")\n    .model(\"gemini-2.5-pro\")\n    .output_col(\"city_poem\")\n    .generation_config(GenerationConfig(temperature=0.7))\n)</textarea>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb TxA6Xc\"></p>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p>Submit this job to your Dataproc cluster:</p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <section>\n    <div class=\"kg99be\" jscontroller=\"vkZm2d\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-text-to-copy=\"gcloud dataproc jobs submit pyspark gemini_spark.py \\ \n  --cluster=my-ml-cluster \\\n  --region=&quot;YOUR_REGION&quot;\" soy-skip=\"\" ssk=\"4:dXrt\">\n     <div jsaction=\"click:VTVhdd\" class=\"GaRnv\"></div>\n     <div jscontroller=\"M2lJBf\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-enable-content-editable-input-style=\"false\" data-enable-line-wrapping=\"\" data-read-only=\"\">\n      <div class=\"hg3Lgc qs41qe BEXrzd\" data-loadingmessage=\"Loading...\" jscontroller=\"GFartf\" jsaction=\"animationend:kWijWc;dyRcpb:dyRcpb\" data-active=\"true\" jsname=\"aZ2wEe\">\n       <div class=\"eBrXtc\" aria-live=\"polite\" jsname=\"vyyg5\">Loading...</div>\n       <div jsname=\"Hxlbvc\" class=\"JdM54e\">\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZqnFk co39ub\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fxjES Cn087\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZHXbZe hfsr6b\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fDBOYb EjXFBf\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n      <div dir=\"ltr\">\n       <textarea jsname=\"bqeLof\" class=\"Fdco1c\">gcloud dataproc jobs submit pyspark gemini_spark.py \\ \n  --cluster=my-ml-cluster \\\n  --region=\"YOUR_REGION\"</textarea>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb TxA6Xc\"></p>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p><b>2. Run inference with PyTorch and TensorFlow models</b></p>\n    <p>In addition to calling Gemini endpoints, the library also allows you to run inference with model files loaded directly from Google Cloud Storage. You can use the PyTorchModelHandler (and a similar handler for TensorFlow) to load your model weights, define a pre-processor, and run inference directly on your worker nodes. This is useful when you want to run batch inference at scale without managing a separate model serving endpoint.</p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <section>\n    <div class=\"kg99be\" jscontroller=\"vkZm2d\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-text-to-copy=\"from google.cloud.dataproc_ml.inference import PyTorchModelHandler\n\n# Get weights and transforms for the model\nweights = ResNet50_Weights.DEFAULT\n\nimage_df = spark.read.format(&quot;binaryFile&quot;).load(&quot;gs://cloud-samples-data/generative-ai/image/&quot;)\n\ndef vectorized_preprocessor(image_bytes_series: pd.Series) -&gt; pd.Series:\n    &quot;&quot;&quot;Applies ResNet50 transforms to a series of image bytes.&quot;&quot;&quot;\n    return image_bytes_series.apply(\n        lambda b: weights.transforms()(Image.open(io.BytesIO(b)).convert(&quot;RGB&quot;))\n    )\n\npytorch_handler = (\n    PyTorchModelHandler()\n    .model_path(&quot;gs://&lt;bucket&gt;/resnet50_full_model.pt&quot;)\n    .input_cols(&quot;content&quot;)\n    .pre_processor(vectorized_preprocess)\n    .set_return_type(ArrayType(FloatType()))\n)\n\npytorch_handler.transform(image_df).show()\" soy-skip=\"\" ssk=\"4:dXrt\">\n     <div jsaction=\"click:VTVhdd\" class=\"GaRnv\">lang-py</div>\n     <div jscontroller=\"M2lJBf\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-language=\"lang-py\" data-enable-content-editable-input-style=\"false\" data-enable-line-wrapping=\"\" data-read-only=\"\">\n      <div class=\"hg3Lgc qs41qe BEXrzd\" data-loadingmessage=\"Loading...\" jscontroller=\"GFartf\" jsaction=\"animationend:kWijWc;dyRcpb:dyRcpb\" data-active=\"true\" jsname=\"aZ2wEe\">\n       <div class=\"eBrXtc\" aria-live=\"polite\" jsname=\"vyyg5\">Loading...</div>\n       <div jsname=\"Hxlbvc\" class=\"JdM54e\">\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZqnFk co39ub\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fxjES Cn087\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX ZHXbZe hfsr6b\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"aopPX fDBOYb EjXFBf\">\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf uEtL3\"></div>\n         <div class=\"LqC3Y\"></div>\n         <div class=\"e2XBBf QR7YS\"></div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n      <div dir=\"ltr\">\n       <textarea jsname=\"bqeLof\" class=\"Fdco1c\">from google.cloud.dataproc_ml.inference import PyTorchModelHandler\n\n# Get weights and transforms for the model\nweights = ResNet50_Weights.DEFAULT\n\nimage_df = spark.read.format(\"binaryFile\").load(\"gs://cloud-samples-data/generative-ai/image/\")\n\ndef vectorized_preprocessor(image_bytes_series: pd.Series) -&gt; pd.Series:\n    \"\"\"Applies ResNet50 transforms to a series of image bytes.\"\"\"\n    return image_bytes_series.apply(\n        lambda b: weights.transforms()(Image.open(io.BytesIO(b)).convert(\"RGB\"))\n    )\n\npytorch_handler = (\n    PyTorchModelHandler()\n    .model_path(\"gs://&lt;bucket&gt;/resnet50_full_model.pt\")\n    .input_cols(\"content\")\n    .pre_processor(vectorized_preprocess)\n    .set_return_type(ArrayType(FloatType()))\n)\n\npytorch_handler.transform(image_df).show()</textarea>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb TxA6Xc\"></p>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <h3><b>Built for performance</b></h3>\n    <p>This library isn't just a simple wrapper. It’s designed for running inference on large Dataproc clusters and includes several optimizations for inference:</p>\n    <ul>\n     <li><b>Vectorized data transfer:</b> We use pandas_udf to efficiently move data between Spark and the Python worker processes.</li>\n     <li><b>Connection re-use:</b> Connections to the endpoint are re-used across partitions to reduce overhead.</li>\n     <li><b>Retry logic:</b> The library automatically handles errors like HTTP 429 (resource exhausted) with exponential backoff and retries.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3><b>Get started</b></h3>\n    <p>You can start using it today by checking out the open-source repository and reading our <a href=\"https://dataproc-ml.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api.html#google.cloud.dataproc.ml.inference.GenAiModelHandler\" target=\"_blank\">documentation</a>.</p>\n    <p>Looking ahead, we plan to add the following features to this library in the coming months.</p>\n    <ol>\n     <li><b>Spark Connect</b> support: This would also allow using above functionalities within <a href=\"https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/use-spark\">BigQuery Studio notebooks</a>.</li>\n     <li><b>Vertex AI integrations</b>: To ease inference, we plan to add more ModelHandlers to:\n      <ol>\n       <li>Directly call a vertex model endpoint for online inference</li>\n       <li>Refer to Vertex models and localize them to Spark workers</li>\n       <li>Refer to models hosted in Vertex Model Garden including embedding models</li>\n      </ol></li>\n     <li><b>More Optimizations</b>: Auto-repartition input dataframes to enhance inference runtime</li>\n     <li><b>Third-party integrations</b>: Refer to open sourced models in HuggingFace</li>\n    </ol>\n    <p>We are actively working on including this library by default in Dataproc on Google Compute Engine ML images and <a href=\"https://cloud.google.com/products/serverless-spark\">Google Cloud Serverless for Apache Spark</a> runtimes.</p>\n    <p>We look forward to seeing what you build! Have feedback or feature requests to further simplify your AI/ML experience on spark? Reach us at dataproc-feedback@google.com.</p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "谷歌推出了开源 Dataproc ML 库，旨在简化 Apache Spark 上的 AI/ML 推理。该库集成了 Gemini 和 Vertex AI 模型，适用于大规模数据处理。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "谷歌推出了开源 Dataproc ML 库，旨在简化 Apache Spark 上的 AI/ML 推理。该库集成了 Gemini 和 Vertex AI 模型，适用于大规模数据处理。",
  "summary": "本文详细介绍了一个新的开源 Python 库 Dataproc ML，旨在简化在 Dataproc 托管集群上运行的 Apache Spark 上的 AI/ML 推理。它解决了数据科学团队在将机器学习模型（特别是来自 Vertex AI 的模型）直接集成到其 Spark 数据管道中时面临的常见挑战，而无需进行大量的自定义开发。该库采用与 SparkML 类似的构建器模式（一种常见的软件设计模式），允许用户配置模型并通过简单的 `.transform()` 方法应用推理。主要用例包括应用生成式 AI 模型（如 Gemini）来执行大规模的分类、提取或摘要等任务，并提供了在 Dataproc 上安装和部署的清晰代码示例。此外，它还支持使用从谷歌云存储加载的 PyTorch 和 TensorFlow 模型运行推理，从而实现批量推理，而无需管理单独的模型服务终端。该库专为性能而构建，具有矢量化数据传输、连接重用和强大的重试逻辑。谷歌计划在未来进行增强，例如支持 Spark Connect、更深入的 Vertex AI 集成（包括在线推理和模型花园）以及第三方模型集成（例如 HuggingFace）。该库计划默认包含在 Dataproc ML 镜像和无服务器 Spark 运行时中，从而显著简化开发人员的端到端 AI/ML 工作流程。",
